article.headline: Florida A&M 81, Norfolk State 71
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- L.C. Robinson led five Rattlers in double figures with 17 points to help Florida A&M defeat Norfolk State 81-71 on Saturday. Florida A&M (8-7, 3-0 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) went on an 11-0 run midway through the first half, and the Rattlers jumped out to a 45-36 halftime lead. Norfolk St. (2-10, 2-1 MEAC) stormed back in the second half, closing within four points, but the Spartans were unable to get any closer. The game was the Rattlers' third conference win. Florida A&M shot 50 percent from the 3-point line. Robinson finished with four 3-pointers. Brian Greene scored 13 points, Darius Glover 12 points, Jon Mason 11 points, and Rome Sanders scored ten. Corey Lyons scored a career high 22 points to lead Norfolk St. Tony Murphy finished with a double-double, scoring 11 points and pulling down ten rebounds. The Spartans also got 13 points from Tynell Dunkley, and 11 from Calvin Brown.
